article.headline: Campbell 72, N.C.-Wilmington 60
article.story: BUIES CREEK, N.C. -- Darren White tallied 32 points and 11 rebounds Saturday to lift Campbell over UNC Wilmington 72-60 and snap a four-game losing streak. Trey Freeman, the only Campbell player to start every game this season, finished with 18 points, six assists and three steals. White and Freeman combined for seven steals for the Camels, who had a season-high 12 steals and held UNC Wilmington to 38.2 percent (21 of 55) shooting. UNC Wilmington (5-7) led by as much as eight points, 22-14, in the first half before watching the advantage dwindle to just 32-31 at halftime. The Seahawks, who went 4 of 9 from deep in the first half, went cold after the break, hitting just 9 of 27 shots, including 1 of 8 from 3-point range. Campbell (4-9) shot 57. 1 percent (16 of 28) in the second half to pull away. Keith Rendleman led UNC Wilmington with 18 points.
